@node Introduction
(First of all, excuse my poor English. The only often used words of that
 language sounds like main() or printf() :-) ).

HideIt V1.20:
-------------

HideIt hides (surprising, ey?) any data within pics.
For that purpose, the information is embedded into the rustling of other
data, this means the lowest bits normally.
The normal beholder/listener cant see/hear any difference, but a program
like HideIt can extract the embedded data.

This is _no_ encryption and not sure to be undiscovered, either.

But in the case of forbidden strong-encryption in your country (like China
or USA) you can send infos anyway without even letting know your human-
right-despicing government that you want to communicate safely.
You are free to pgp-encrypt your data before you embed it, only for the
case that it is discoverd...

Since the program is fairly young, it only supports the "IFF-24"-format
_without_ packing.
You can create this for example in Photogenics by choosing "IFF-24" as
save-format and in its options "save as non-packed IFF" (or so, I dont
know the English version).
The data-format isnt that important, by the way, because you can convert
any picture-format accordingly.
There are planned more formats, but this is a long-winded complex process,
not to compare with normal datatyes-support, so the resonance counts.


P.S.: There is another program of mine in the Aminet called
      misc/sci/Wator_1.27.lha (or newer version). It's a graphics-supported
      hunter-and-booty-simulation.
      Simply download (100K) and have fun !!

      I'm pleased to get any response, no matter whether
      flame or praise. See guide for address.
@endnode

@node Usage

Usage of HideIt:
----------------

After start you see a GUI. There you can choose three files and select
from "Hide", "Extract" and "About". The latter one contains basic usage
information, too.
On the bottom, there is a small status-box (where the programs informs you
about the process, like "ready") and above a bigger info-box (where
some important picture-infos are located).
Heavy error causing adequate requesters.

On Hiding you have to specify the following:

        Source.........A IFF-24-file with RunLength-packing switched off.
                       This is a normal picture file.
                       It can be created by choosing in Photogenics'
                       save-modul "IFF-24" and in its options "save un-
                       compressed IFF-files" (or so).
                       At this time, no other format is supported. See
                       @{"Introduction" link Introduction} for the reasons.
                       But thats no problem, because every pic can
                       converted accordingly.

        Destination....Here the Source with the data embedded is saved.
                       The size is exactly like the size of the source.
                       !!!! If this file is already existent, it will be
                       overwritten without any question !!!!

        Data...........The data to hide. Of course, it can be only a part
                       of the sorces' size big. Because at this time only
                       the red channel is used for embedding, the maximum
                       size is

                           (source-width/8)*source-height-8 bytes.

                       Example: 768x480 pixel -> 46072 databytes



On Extracting you have to specify the following:

        Source.........IFF-24-picture with embedded data

        Destination....(without any meaning)

        Data...........Here the extracted data are saved. If there are no
                       data was hidden, HideIt tries to extract the maximum
                       data the picture could have embedded.
                       !!!! If this file is already existent, it will be
                       overwritten without any question !!!!

At this time, only unpacked IFF-24-files are supported.
See @{"Introduction" link Introduction} for the reasons.

If you like the prog or not, send a mail to:

                         uhoesel@freenet.de .

This is my second Aminet-prog, so I would like to get some mails.
The resonance will determine the motivation for following versions...
@endnode

